			<h1 class="title">3/19/2020 18:39hrs – Covid19 Update – School Activities Cancelled</h1>
				<div class="post-meta">
		<p class="meta-info">
			Posted  on Mar 13, 2020 in <a href="http://www.napoleon.k12.nd.us/category/announcments/" rel="category tag">Announcments</a> | <a href="http://www.napoleon.k12.nd.us/2020/03/13/school-activities-cancelled/#respond">0 comments</a>		</p>
	</div> <!-- end .post-meta -->
			
			
			<p style="text-align: right;">19 March 2020</p>
<p><span data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="16">Due to the COVID pandemic, Governor Doug Burgum has announced to close all K12 schools in North Dakota until April 1<sup data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="13.333333015441895">st</sup>. Next week, our staff will be working on eLearning platforms and ideas how we will educate our students for the rest of the year. I will send out further instruction next week that will detail when you need come to school and pick up books, supplies, etc. Please wait for instructions before coming to school. We will still have NO public access to the school, NO access to the weight room and NO school activities until further notice. Do to the lack of students eating breakfast, we will discontinue serving breakfast but we will extend our lunch hours from 11 am to 1 pm. This is free to any student that wishes to eat. </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="16">I emailed out a survey for parents to fill out. I received 86 responses so far and waiting on 35 others. Please check your email, including your spam for my email. If you still didn’t receive an email, you need to call Richard Bjerklie at <a href="tel:754-2244">754-2244</a> ASAP (leave a message if no one answers) or email <a href="mailto:Richard.Bjerklie@napoleon.k12.nd.us" data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="16">Richard.Bjerklie@napoleon.k12.nd.us</a>We have to be in contact with you in order to see who needs internet access at your home. We have companies that are willing to provide access to free internet for a couple of months, but we need to know who does not have internet access. Here is the link to the survey. </span><a href="https://forms.gle/oNUDyzKkE42g2QRB8" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://forms.gle/oNUDyzKkE42g2QRB8&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1584747029913000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEgqqMfi0DthL74uD9epKLywJ5w6w" data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="16">https://forms.gle/oNUDyzKkE42g2QRB8</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span data-removefontsize="true" data-originalcomputedfontsize="16">Please keep checking the school website and our Facebook page for updates. Updates will also be shared by email.</span></p>
<p>16 March 2020</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you all for your patience and understanding as we all adjust to the COVID-19 virus. I know there will be a lot of questions, please understand that everything is being done in an attempt to protect our most vulnerable population. Here are some updates as of March 16, 2020:</p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">Please practice “Social Distancing” to the best of your ability. Please encourage your children not to go to public meeting places during this time while continuing to wash their hands and practice good hygiene methods.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">We are still serving breakfast from 8:00-8:45 and lunch from 11:00-12:00.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">There will be NO public access to the school.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">There will be NO access to the weight room until further notice.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">All after school activities are cancelled until further notice.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;">Additional information will be provided as we receive further guidance from Governor Doug Burgum’s office and the North Dakota Department of Health.</li>
</ul>
<p>15 March 2020</p>
<p>Due to the COVID pandemic, Governor Doug Burgum has announced to close all K12 schools in North Dakota for this week. All activities including Parent-Teacher Conferences are cancelled. We will serve a to go breakfast from 8:00-8:45 am and a bag lunch from 11:00-12:00. All students are welcome to eat if needed. We will have updates throughout the week posted on our Facebook page, webpage, parent emails, and our all-call alert system. Thank you for your patience in this unprecedented time.</p>
<p>13 Mar 2020</p>
<p>Special Announcement: Due to Emergency Declaration issued by President Trump, the NDHSAA has suspended all extra curricular activities immediately. All tournaments, fine arts competitions, and sporting events are all immediately suspended indefinately.</p>
<p>Napoleon Basketball Booster tournament cancelled (Sat 14th March)</p>
<p>No Practices for any extracurricular activity</p>
<p>No FFA events</p>
<p>No DECA events</p>
<p>No open gyms or school related extracurricular gatherings</p>
